  <text>
    <body>
      <ab type="lido:objectWorkType">Poster</ab>
      <ab subtype="creation" type="lido:event">
        <date>1927 after</date>
      </ab>
      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">The double-framed poster announces the screening of the feature film ‘Kralj čarlstona’ (King of Charleston) in the ‘Kasina’ cinema – the premiere of ‘Belgrade’s first feature’ with a member of the Belgrade operetta, Ms. Odžić, in the leading role. In addition, the poster announces that the film ‘Ljubav kroz telefon’ (Love through the telephone) – originally ‘Das Fräulein vom Amt’ – about the passion of a switchboard girl starring Mary Johnson and André Mattoni, will also be screened.</ab>
      <ab subtype="comment" type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">‘Kralj čarlstona’ was directed by Yugoslav producer and director Kosta Novaković (1927). ‘Das Fräulein vom Amt’ (The switchboard operator) was directed by Hanns Schwarz.</ab>
